		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			   I would like to say one thing about &quot;trains&quot; - they really exist as a bug in the game and not as a true ambush.  Trains are simply a bunch of monsters sharing the same space while running after you.  This is a result of the horrible clipping problems in everquest.  Castles are build upon the principle that enemy invaders can only proceed one or two at a time through a narrow entrance while the defenders all have a shot at the enemy.  If you've ever visited blackburrow, you'll notice that gnolls often merge into a 8 armed, 8 legged, 4 headed being sharing the same space.  If everquest were designed with mob clipping in play, it would be possible for a level 12 warrior to mop up each gnoll one at a time while a cleric behind him keep healing him.  That's how the ancient Athenians defeated an army of invading Persians, by forcing them to fight in a narrow cliffside... Although the Persian army was much more massive, the Athenian (or ancient Greeks) were slightly a little stronger and had better armor, and they managed to take out a huge chunk of the Persian army before loosing that battle... If that battle took part on everquest, the persians would have just merged into an 4000 thousand arm/leg being and massacred the athenians one by one.<BR>
<BR>
   How interesting it would be to have you and your partner run from a horde of lions and run into a small inn and NOT have them attack you through the walls - but instead growl viciously at the door.. Or a brave warrior chopping down orc after orc while in the narrow corridor of crushbone.<BR>
 <BR>
   Just my two coppers...<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

			</font>
	
